      <h2>The One Rule That Covers 80% of Timing</h2>

      <p>
        If you only take one thing from this post: <strong>get 30g of protein at breakfast.</strong>
      </p>

      <p>
        It's the highest-leverage timing move available to most men over 40. Not because breakfast is magic — but because it's where the gap is largest and where fixing it has the biggest downstream effect on the whole day. Men who hit 30g at breakfast consistently hit their daily target. Men who don't are almost always short by dinner.
      </p>

      <p>
        The <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/30-gram-protein-rule/">30-gram rule</a> is built around exactly this idea — one number per meal, starting at breakfast, repeated three to four times a day. Everything else on this page is refinement on top of that foundation.
      </p>

